  "title": "Quantity Surveyor",
  "description": "<p>Prepare and manage project cost estimates, budgets, and cash flow throughout the project lifecycle</p><p>Handle tendering processes, including preparation, evaluation, and contract award</p><p>Prepare interim valuations, progress claims, variations, and final accounts</p><p>Review subcontractor quotations, negotiate terms, and manage cost control</p><p>Monitor project costs and identify potential risks and cost-saving opportunities</p><p>Coordinate closely with project managers, consultants, and subcontractors</p><p>Ensure compliance with contract terms, specifications, and company policies</p><p>Prepare cost reports and provide financial advice to management<br />Diploma or Bachelor’s degree in Quantity Surveying, Construction Management, or related discipline</p><p>Familiar with standard forms of contract (e.g. <strong>SIA, PSSCOC</strong>)</p><p>Good knowledge of measurement, cost control, and contract administration</p><p>Proficient in MS Excel and QS-related software</p><p>Strong analytical, negotiation, and communication skills</p><p>Able to work independently and as part of a team</p>",
